<TITLE> Mizan remanded for questioning </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 16 (bdnews24.com)Police on Saturday remanded Jahidur Rahman Mizan, the bomb expert of banned Islamist outfit Jama'atul Mujahideen Bangladesh, in custody for seven days to question him. The chief metropolitan magistrate, Dhaka Syeda Minhajum Munira put Boma Mizan, as he is commonly known, on remand after the police produced asked for 10 days. Mizan was captured on Thursday evening at his Pirerbag residence in the capital's Mirpur. On his confessions, RAB conducted a four-hour raid on his apartment and recovered two grenades, a live bomb and a pistol with two magazines. During the raid that started at 10pm, his wife Sharmin Haque Lata exploded a grenade which blew off her wrist. She and her two children were sent to the Dhaka Medical College Hospital. bd
